cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with wireless information transmission and explores the optimum wireless information transmission blocklength, which is a key concept in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses a wireless-powered communication network and proposes a rate control strategy to cope with reliability and delay constraints. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a rate control strategy that exploits battery charge information to improve the performance of the system. This involves control of the system and falls under the domain of systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the impact of a greater number of antennas at the destination on the performance of the system. This is relevant to multimedia applications that require high data rates and reliable transmission. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper uses mathematical models and closed-form approximations to analyze the performance of the system. This falls under the domain of computational engineering, finance, and science.
